    {
      "text": "This phase aims to make Exaix fully user-configurable by externalizing all hardcoded magic numbers, magic words, and lists from the source code. The goal is to move all user-facing configuration (timeouts, limits, model names, provider lists, etc.) into TOML configuration files (primarily `exa.config.toml` and `exa.config.sample.toml`), and all internal constants into dedicated `constants.ts` modules. For CLI/TUI-specific constants, separate config files will be considered. This will empower users to adapt Exaix to their needs without modifying source code, improving maintainability, portability, and user experience.",
